[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'precise photography is key to achieving strong [music] visual fidelity in the Gaussian Splatting reconstruction. Uh for this project, I captured the restaurant interior using a single full-frame camera, a 14-mm lens, and a'

[01:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tripod. Sharpening and color correction of the images were also necessary. Uh to maintain strong depth of field, I closed'

[01:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the aperture down to F10, and walked through the entire space &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; and taking the images. Beyond its interior, [music] the'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'restaurant offers beautifully crafted and carefully presented dishes, which are also very delicious. So, on a separate [music] day, I scanned part of the menu. Uh the dishes have to be captured while'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'they were freshly prepared, so I built a small rig with three synchronized cameras that allowed me to photograph everything directly at the restaurant. To keep the framing consistent, I used two lasers as a simple aiming system to'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ensure the dishes stayed properly positioned during the capture. It worked surprisingly well. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[02:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; This rig made the scanning process much faster, allowing me to capture every dish in just a matter of minutes while [music] preserving the freshness and presentation of the food. To create an immersive experience that'

[02:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'can be accessed online on your phone or desktop computer, I got help from two very talented people, Hannes and Leo. Both are exceptional 3D artists, technologists, and Gaussian'

